2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 62
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of Joseph
Cassimere.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of
3 Louisiana upon the death of Joseph Cassimere.
4 WHEREAS, it is with deep regret and profound sorrow that the citizens of St. Landry
5 Parish, and the state of Louisiana, learned that the Almighty God in His infinite wisdom
6 called Joseph Cassimere on February 12, 2026, at the age of seventy-six to eternal rest; and
7 WHEREAS, Matthew 25:23 says "Well done good and faithful servant!" and many
8 who describe Joseph Cassimere as a devoted husband, loving father, caring brother, lifelong
9 educator, dedicated farmer, colleague, and member of the Mohorn Missionary Baptist
10 Church agree that he lived and earned that reputation; and
11 WHEREAS, Cassimere attended Southern University A&M College in Baton Rouge,
12 Louisiana obtaining his Bachelor of Science Degree in Recreational Arts in 1973; completed
13 the Teacher Education Program at Southern University in Baton Rouge in 1976; earned a
14 Master of Educational Leadership from Southern University in Baton Rouge in 1978, and
15 pursued an additional thirty hours of graduate coursework; and
16 WHEREAS, Cassimere's faithfulness over his God given talents resulted in
17 additional responsibilities and he devoted forty-seven years of service in the field of
18 education, rising from the classroom to serve as a teacher, assistant principal, and the first
